#Text=And a happy society .
#Text=At least I found a lot of people who were very content .
#Text=They may not have an easy life , but they were quite content .
#Text=They have their honor .
#Text=They have their dignity .
#Text=They 're not a serf class to the aristocracy .
#Text=People dancing in the streets at night .
#Text=I went out at night and I saw a lot of that .
#Text=That 's true .
#Text=They have their values .
#Text=And friendly .
#Text=And friendly .
#Text=Much more than those Cubans in Miami .
#Text=My friend I was with was Colombian from Miami , and he made the exact same observation .
#Text=He had a prejudice against Cubans from his time in Miami and he said , " These people are n't anything like the Cubans in Miami . "
#Text=On Chinese gay bars
#Text=Do you have a favorite country you have visited ?
#Text=Well I think the city I found most interesting was Beijing .
#Text=You talk about China a lot .
#Text=I found that really a place that changes every year .
#Text=And it 's what you can do .
#Text=That 's one city .
#Text=I spent so much time in Europe when I was young .
#Text=Is it interesting to you to watch China change ?
#Text=Yeah , I read everything that 's in the papers about China .
#Text=I completed a story today about how the Bush administration was being used by China .
#Text=Do you get tired of going to the same region and then you 're like , ‘ I need to go to Asia for a while ? '
#Text=That 's right .
#Text=That happened to me in 1998 .
#Text=Kind of interesting .
#Text=I was able to see without being interrupted with interpretation because I could n't understand anything .
#Text=I so so enjoyed being places I 've never been before like Kuala Lumpur , Singapore , not Hong Kong , but other places .
#Text=You asked me about Beijing .
#Text=It 's the most interesting city because it 's an international city in which there is this history going back hundreds and hundreds of years of turmoil , accommodation .
#Text=They are such entrepreneurial people on the lowest level to the highest level , the Chinese .
#Text=And they 're so quick in understanding how to survive and there are so many of them .
#Text=God , there are so many of them .
#Text=Have you been to Asia ?
#Text=I have n't been to Asia .
#Text=It does n't particularly interest me all that much .
#Text=There are countries I would like to see , Cambodia being one .
#Text=South America is one of the areas that I am most interested to explore because I speak Spanish .
#Text=You do ?
#Text=I do n't speak anything .
#Text=I felt similarly when I first got out of Beijing .
#Text=I said Beijing is an interesting city because it 's international , because it has the press from around the world and the political representation of the whole world in that capitol city .

#Text=But at night , especially if you have some Chinese friends who speak English so you 're able to have them tell you a little bit about what you 're seeing as they take you around and you go to clubs .
#Text=What first impressed me in Beijing was the great number of gay men , and women I guess , but gay men who had clubs , gay bars in Beijing .
#Text=I do n't read this in the paper .
#Text=But what impressed me was how open it is .
#Text=One called Club Vogue .
#Text=I went there .
